         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Ferndale ¶ nr Double Bay ¶ My dear Baron Müeller ¶  ¶ I send you specimens of a Dampera ¶  but I do not know if it is the one you want. It seems in growth exactly like the one I drew (&amp; which Dr Wooll...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.08.00a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Harriet Scott</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter dated on basis of its evident relationship to H. Scott to M, 15 August 1881 (in this edition as 81-08-15b). It was certainly written prior to Scott’s marriage to C. W. Morgan in 1882.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Ferndale</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">nr Double Bay<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sydney.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron Müeller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send you specimens of a Dampera<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dampiera</seg>.</p>
               </note> but I do not know if it is the one you want. It seems in growth exactly like the one I drew (&amp; which Dr Woolls called a var. of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Stricta</hi>
               </seg>) &amp; yet the flowers are different — The specimen I first got had only <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> flower that was open on it. The others were all withered &amp; dead, &amp; this <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one flower</hi>
               </seg> I drew from was a particularly fine one of a very deep blue &amp; with the upper petal <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all in one</hi>
               </seg>. I was so very much struck with the graceful little plant that I drew this living flower in several positions putting them on places in the plant where there were dead ones — If these specimens I now send are the same as that I drew then the flower must have been a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">malformation</hi>
               </seg> as these I see have the upper petal cut in two. The buds too, &amp; there were lots, were very pretty &amp; all tipped with deep blue —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>These plants I have sent you by the same post were all got at Double Bay, growing in deep Shade under Banksia &amp; other trees, &amp; all in the small Ferns and old dry grass — Some of the plants you will see are of great length but I could not find a single seed vessel —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The flowers enclosed were broken off the plants I send you —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Tell me if I am to get you any more, &amp; if it is the one you want as then I will send you per post flowers in alcohol. I know where to find more —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You sent Baron Maclay<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nikolai Miklouho-Maclay.</p>
               </note> &amp; my sister your photograph with all your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">honours</hi>
               </seg> on, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">won't you give me one</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am writing to catch todays post.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Very sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Harriet Scott</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Damperi%20Stricta">Damperi Stricta</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
